All Classes

Class Description
AddEventPerformanceCommand
AddEventPerformanceCommand allows EntertainmentProviders to add performances to an existing event that they have created.
BookEventCommand
BookEventCommand allows Consumers to book tickets for a specific EventPerformance.
Booking
Booking represents a booking made by a Consumer for a TicketedEvent EventPerformance.
BookingState
BookingState is a concrete implementation of IBookingState.
BookingStatus  
CancelBookingCommand
CancelBookingCommand allows Consumers to cancel a Booking given its unique booking number.
CancelEventCommand
CancelEventCommand allows EntertainmentProviders to cancel a previously added Event (and all corresponding EventPerformances).
Consumer
Consumer represents a user of the application, who can browse Events and book TicketedEvents.
ConsumerPreferences
A set of Covid-19 preferences that Consumers can save in their profile and filter Events based on them.
Context
Context is a wrapper around the entire app state.
Controller
Controller is the main external interface of this application.
CreateEventCommand
CreateEventCommand contains common behaviour shared by commands to create different kinds of events.
CreateNonTicketedEventCommand
CreateNonTicketedEventCommand allows EntertainmentProviders to create NonTicketedEvents.
CreateTicketedEventCommand
CreateTicketedEventCommand allows EntertainmentProviders to create TicketedEvents.
CustomPreTaglet
A taglet to allow the "custom.pre" tag in JavaDoc, which shows a bullet point list of preconditions that a method checks.
EntertainmentProvider
EntertainmentProvider is a user of the application, who represents an organisation that hosts Events.
EntertainmentProviderSystem
Interface for the external EntertainmentProviderSystem, it allows informing about changes made to events and bookings on our system, and querying for up-to-date number of available tickets for a given EventPerformance (in case ticket sales are made outside this system).
Event
Event is an abstraction, containing common state and behaviour that NonTicketedEvents and TicketedEvents share.
EventPerformance
EventPerformance represents an event taking place at a concrete place, date, and time.
EventState
EventState is a concrete implementation of IEventState.
EventStatus  
EventType  
GetAvailablePerformanceTicketsCommand
GetAvailablePerformanceTicketsCommand allows users (even if they are not logged in) to see up-to-date information about how many tickets are available for a specific TicketedEvent EventPerformance.
GovernmentReport1Command  
GovernmentReport2Command  
GovernmentRepresentative
GovernmentRepresentative is a user who represents the government.
IBookingState
IBookingState is an interface representing the portion of application state that contains all the Booking information.
ICommand
ICommand is the interface implemented by all commands.
IEventState
IEventState is an interface representing the portion of application state that contains all the Event information.
ISponsorshipState
ISponsorshipState is an interface representing the portion of the application that contains all the SponsorshipRequest information.
IUserState
IUserState is an interface representing the portion of the application that contains all the registered User information.
ListConsumerBookingsCommand
ListConsumerBookingsCommand allows a logged-in Consumer to get a list of all their own Bookings.
ListEventBookingsCommand
ListEventBookingsCommand allows an event organiser (EntertainmentProvider) or GovernmentRepresentative to get a list of all Bookings for a chosen TicketedEvent.
ListEventsCommand
ListEventsCommand allows anyone to get a list of Events available on the system.
ListEventsOnGivenDateCommand
ListEventsOnGivenDateCommand extends ListEventsCommand to allow retrieving Events on a given particular LocalDateTime +- 1 day
ListSponsorshipRequestsCommand
ListSponsorshipRequestsCommand allows GovernmentRepresentatives to get a list of registered SponsorshipRequests.
LogEntry
LogEntry is a single entry in the log kept by the singleton Logger.
Logger
Logger is a singleton that can be retrieved from anywhere to add log entries.
LoginCommand
LoginCommand allows a previously registered User to log in to the system by providing their login details.
LogoutCommand
LogoutCommand allows the currently logged in User to log out
MockEntertainmentProviderSystem
A mock implementation of EntertainmentProviderSystem, substituting real systems for testing purposes.
MockPaymentSystem
A mock implementation of PaymentSystem for testing purposes.
NonTicketedEvent
NonTicketedEvent is an event open to everyone, it does not accept bookings.
PaymentSystem
Interface for the external PaymentSystem (e.g., PayPal, Transferwise, or similar).
RegisterConsumerCommand
RegisterConsumerCommand allows users to register a new Consumer account on the system.
RegisterEntertainmentProviderCommand
RegisterEntertainmentProviderCommand allows users to register a new EntertainmentProvider account on the system.
RespondSponsorshipCommand
RespondSponsorshipCommand allows GovernmentRepresentatives to accept or reject a pending SponsorshipRequest.
SponsorshipRequest
SponsorshipRequests can be optionally created when creating a TicketedEvent.
SponsorshipState
SponsorshipState is a concrete implementation of ISponsorshipState.
SponsorshipStatus  
TicketedEvent
TicketedEvent represents an event that can be booked by Consumers.
UpdateConsumerProfileCommand
UpdateConsumerProfileCommand allows Consumers to update their account details and change the default Covid-19 preferences.
UpdateEntertainmentProviderProfileCommand
UpdateEntertainmentProviderProfileCommand allows EntertainmentProviders to update their account details in the system.
UpdateProfileCommand
UpdateProfileCommand contains common behaviour shared between profile update commands
User
User is an abstraction, containing common state and behaviours shared by different kinds of users: Consumers, EntertainmentProviders, and GovernmentRepresentatives.
UserState
UserState is a concrete implementation of IUserState.
